288// Keys
289enum OBJ_KEYS {
290OBJ_TYPE = 0, //value type - int: See OBJ_TYPE_VALUES
291OBJ_NAME = 1, //value type - str: See OBJ_NAME_VALUES
292OBJ_LAYER = 2, //value type - str: "USER", "DEFINED", "STRINGS", etc...
293OBJ_COLOR = 3, //value type - int: 0-255 //TODO: Use color chart in formats/format-dxf.h for this
294OBJ_LTYPE = 4, //value type - int: See OBJ_LTYPE_VALUES
295OBJ_LWT = 5, //value type - int: 0-27
296OBJ_RUBBER = 6 //value type - int: See OBJ_RUBBER_VALUES
297};

585typedef struct UiObject_ {
586 char fname[200]; /*< \todo document this */
587 char command[200]; /*< \todo document this */
588 bool firstRun; /*< If this UiObject has been put through the
589 user interaction processor. */
590 EmbVector controlPoints[10]; /*< Storage for however many Rubber Points the
591 design needs. */
592 char controlPointLabels[10][200]; /*< Storage for the labels for the Rubber Points
593 using the same indexing. */
594 int n_controlPoints; /*< The number of entries in the controlPoints
595 and controlPointsLabels. */
596 int numPoints; /*< The number of points if we consider the object as a Polygon. */
597 int minPoints; /*< The minimum number of points needed to make the
598 polygon look somewhat like the design. */
599 int maxPoints; /*< The maximum number of points before adding more will
600 do nothing but slow down the program. */
601 EmbVector center; /*< Where the polygon is centered. */
602 EmbVector scale; /*< The scale of the object: note that the default
603 may not be (1.0, 1.0). */
604 EmbReal rotation; /*< \todo document this */
605 unsigned int mode; /*< The mode argument records what kind of design we are
606 using and how to interact with it. */
607 char path_desc[1000]; /*< The SVG style path spec. */
608 char text[200]; /*< The text to be rendered to the scene. */
609 int textJustify; /*< One of the JUSTIFY_* constants representing what kind
610 of alignment to use. */
611 char textFont[200]; /*< The file name of the font to use. */
612 float textHeight; /*< The text height. */
613 float textRotation; /*< The rotation of the text in the scene. */
614 GLuint texture_id; /*< Pointer to a texture that may be rendered to the object. */
615 char id[200]; /*< \todo document this */
616 int pattern_index; /*< \todo document this */
617 char type[200]; /*< \todo document this */
618 int object_index; /*< \todo document this */
619 bool selectable; /*< \todo document this */
620 EmbColor color; /*< \todo document this */
621} UiObject;

1177int
1178main(int argc, char *argv[])
1179{
1180 char command[200];
1181 strcpy(command, "open");
1182 parse_command(argc, argv, command);
1183 if (!settings.running) {
1184 return 0;
1185 }
1186
1187 strcpy(settings_file, "./settings.toml");
1188 read_settings(settings_file);
1189 load_configuration();
1190
1191 if (strcmp(command, "open")) {
1192 actuator(command);
1193 }
1194
1195 EmbColor ruler_color_ = {150, 170, 0};
1196 EmbColor black_color_ = {0, 0, 0};
1197 EmbColor white_color_ = {255, 255, 255};
1198 settings.ruler_color = embColor_to_int(ruler_color_, 255);
1199 settings.ticks_color = embColor_to_int(black_color_, 255);
1200 settings.grid_color = embColor_to_int(black_color_, 255);
1201 settings.shine_color = embColor_to_int(white_color_, 20);
1202
1203 int width = 1080;
1204 int height = 576;
1205 if (!glfwInit()) {
1206 log_debug("ERROR: Failed to initialise GLFW.");
1207 return 2;
1208 }
1209 char title[200];
1210 sprintf(title, "Embroidermodder %s", settings.version);
1211 GLFWwindow *window = glfwCreateWindow(width, height, title, NULL, NULL);
1212 if (!window) {
1213 log_debug("Failed to create GLFW window.");
1214 glfwTerminate();
1215 return 1;
1216 }
1217 glfwMakeContextCurrent(window);
1218
1219 char font_file[200];
1220 sprintf(font_file, "%sfonts/SourceSans3-Regular.ttf", settings.assets_dir);
1221
1222 setup_imgui(window);
1223 set_style(font_file);
1224 load_textures(settings.texture_list);
1225
1226 while (!glfwWindowShouldClose(window)) {
1227 glfwPollEvents();
1228
1229 imgui_new_frame();
1230
1231 setup_main_widget();
1232
1233 strcpy(menu_action, "");
1234
1239 if (begin_menu_bar()) {
1240 load_menu("File");
1241 load_menu("Edit");
1242 load_menu("View");
1243 load_menu("Tools");
1244 load_menu("Draw");
1245 load_menu("Window");
1246 load_menu("Settings");
1247 load_menu("Help");
1248 end_menu_bar();
1249 }
1250
1252 load_toolbar("File");
1253 same_line();
1254 load_toolbar("Edit");
1255 same_line();
1256 load_toolbar("Help");
1257 same_line();
1258 load_toolbar("Icon");
1259 same_line();
1260 load_toolbar("Draw");
1261
1262 load_toolbar("Zoom");
1263 same_line();
1264 load_toolbar("Pan");
1265 same_line();
1266 load_toolbar("View");
1267
1268 load_toolbar("Layer");
1269 same_line();
1270 load_toolbar("Properties");
1271
1272 load_toolbar("Text");

1384
1416int
1417run_script(const char *filename)
1418{
1419 char line[200];
1420 FILE *f;
1421 int line_pos = 0;
1422 f = fopen(filename, "r");
1423 char c;
1424 while (fread(&c, 1, 1, f)) {
1425 if (c != '\n') {
1426 line[line_pos] = c;
1427 line_pos++;
1428 }
1429 else {
1430 line[line_pos+1] = 0;
1431 actuator(line);
1432 line_pos = 0;
1433 }
1434 }
1435 fclose(f);
1436 return 0;
1437}
1438
1446EmbReal
1447random_uniform(void)
1448{
1449 int r = rand() % 100000;
1450 return 0.00001*r;
1451}
1452
1463int
1464roundToMultiple(int roundUp, int numToRound, int multiple)
1465{
1466 if (multiple == 0) {
1467 return numToRound;
1468 }
1469 int remainder = numToRound % multiple;
1470 if (remainder == 0) {
1471 return numToRound;
1472 }
1473
1474 if (numToRound < 0 && roundUp) {
1475 return numToRound - remainder;
1476 }
1477 if (roundUp) {
1478 return numToRound + multiple - remainder;
1479 }
1480 //else round down
1481 if (numToRound < 0 && !roundUp) {
1482 return numToRound - multiple - remainder;
1483 }
1484 return numToRound - remainder;
1485}
1486
1495bool
1496willUnderflowInt32(int32_t a, int32_t b)
1497{
1498 assert(LLONG_MAX>INT_MAX);
1499 int64_t c = (int64_t)a-b;
1500 return c < INT_MIN || c > INT_MAX;
1501}
1502
1511bool
1512willOverflowInt32(int32_t a, int32_t b)
1513{
1514 assert(LLONG_MAX>INT_MAX);
1515 int64_t c = (int64_t)a+b;
1516 return c < INT_MIN || c > INT_MAX;
1517}

1526bool
1527valid_file_format(char *fname)
1528{
1529 if (fname[0] == 0) {
1530 return false;
1531 }
1532 if (emb_identify_format(fname) >= 0) {
1533 return true;
1534 }
1535 return false;
1536}

1555static void
1556c_split(char input[200], int *argc, char argv[10][200])
1557{
1558 *argc = 0;
1559 char buffer[200];
1560 strcpy(buffer, input);
1561 char *p = strtok(buffer, " ");
1562 for (int i=0; i<10; i++) {
1563 strcpy(argv[*argc], p);
1564 (*argc)++;
1565 p = strtok(NULL, " ");
1566 if (p == NULL) {
1567 break;
1568 }
1569 }
1570}

1583EmbReal
1584emb_clamp(EmbReal lower, EmbReal x, EmbReal upper)
1585{
1586 if (lower > x) {
1587 return lower;
1588 }
1589 if (upper < x) {
1590 return upper;
1591 }
1592 return x;
1593}

1668static void
1669open_file_dialog(void)
1670{
1671 char separator = '/';
1672 #if _WIN32
1673 separator = '\\';
1674 #endif
1675 // char typed_filename[400];
1676 begin_ui("Open File", 600, 400);
1677 tinydir_dir dir;
1678 if (tinydir_open_sorted(&dir, current_directory) == -1) {
1679 translated_text("Failed to open directory.");
1680 end_ui();
1681 return;
1682 }
1683 int n_columns = 1 + dir.n_files/5;
1684 columns(n_columns, "files");
1685 for (size_t i=0; i<dir.n_files; i++) {
1686 tinydir_file file;
1687 tinydir_readfile_n(&dir, &file, i);
1688 if (button(file.name)) {
1689 if (file.is_dir) {
1690 sprintf(current_directory, "%s%c%s",
1691 current_directory, separator, file.name);
1692 simplify_path(current_directory);
1693 }
1694 else {
1695 sprintf(to_open, "%s%s", current_directory, file.name);
1696 }
1697 }
1698 tinydir_next(&dir);
1699 if (i%5 == 4) {
1700 next_column();
1701 }
1702 }
1703 end_columns();
1704 display_text(current_directory);
1705 display_text(to_open);
1706 //ImGui::InputText("", typed_filename, 100);
1707 if (button("Open")) {
1708 char cmd[200];
1709 sprintf(cmd, "open %s", to_open);
1710 log_debug(to_open);
1711 actuator(cmd);
1712 settings.show_open_file_dialog = false;
1713 }
1714 same_line();
1715 if (button("Cancel")) {
1716 settings.show_open_file_dialog = false;
1717 }
1718 tinydir_close(&dir);
1719 end_ui();
1720}

1725static void
1726parse_command(int argc, char *argv[], char command[200])
1727{
1728 for (int i=1; i<argc; i++) {
1729 char *s = argv[i];
1730 if (streq(s, "--local-boot") || streq(s, "-L")) {
1731 strcpy(settings.assets_dir, argv[i+1]);
1732 printf("Booting from \"%s\".\n", settings.assets_dir);
1733 i++;
1734 continue;
1735 }
1736 if (streq(s, "--debug") || streq(s, "-d")) {
1737 settings.debug_mode = 1;
1738 printf("DEBUG MODE\n");
1739 continue;
1740 }
1741 if (streq(s, "--help") || streq(s, "-h")) {
1742 usage();
1743 settings.running = false;
1744 }
1745 if (streq(s, "--version") || streq(s, "-v")) {
1746 /* For scripts that need the version string */
1747 printf("%s", settings.version);
1748 settings.running = false;
1749 }
1750 if (streq(s, "--test")) {
1751 settings.testing = true;
1752 continue;
1753 }
1754 strcat(command, " ");
1755 strcat(command, s);
1756 }
1757
1758 get_current_directory(settings.current_directory);
1759}
1760
1761
1767static void
1768simplify_path(char *path)
1769{
1770 char storage[200];
1771 strcpy(storage, path);
1772 char *separator = "/";
1773 #if _WIN32
1774 separator = "\\";
1775 #endif
1776 char tokens_to_use[30][100];
1777 int n_tokens = 0;
1778 char *token = strtok(storage, separator);
1779 while (token != NULL) {
1780 if (streq(token, "..")) {
1781 n_tokens--;
1782 }
1783 if (strcmp(token, "..") && strcmp(token, ".") && strcmp(token, "")) {
1784 strcpy(tokens_to_use[n_tokens], token);
1785 n_tokens++;
1786 }
1787 token = strtok(NULL, separator);
1788 }
1789
1790 #if _WIN32
1791 strcpy(path, "");
1792 #else
1793 strcpy(path, "/");
1794 #endif
1795
1796 for (int i=0; i<n_tokens; i++) {
1797 strcat(path, tokens_to_use[i]);
1798 if (i < n_tokens-1) {
1799 strcat(path, separator);
1800 }
1801 }
1802}
1803
1807static void
1808load_menu(const char *menu_label)
1809{
1810 if (begin_menu(menu_label)) {
1811 Dictionary *dict = dictionary_from_index(menu_layout, menu_label);
1812 if (dict == NULL) {
1813 end_menu();
1814 return;
1815 }
1816 for (int i=0; i<dict->length; i++) {
1817 DictionaryEntry line = dict->data[i];
1818 if (!strcmp(line.key, "---")) {
1819 menu_separator();
1820 continue;
1821 }
1822 if (!strcmp(line.value, "submenu")) {
1823 load_menu(line.key);
1824 continue;
1825 }
1826 if (menu_item(line.key)) {
1827 strcpy(menu_action, line.value);
1828 }
1829 }
1830 end_menu();
1831 }
1832}
1833
1837GLuint
1838gen_gl_texture(uint8_t* data, int w, int h, int wrap)
1839{
1840 GLuint texture;
1841
1842 glGenTextures(1, &texture);
1843 glBindTexture(GL_TEXTURE_2D, texture);
1844 glTexParameteri(GL_TEXTURE_2D, GL_TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER, GL_LINEAR);
1845 glTexParameteri(GL_TEXTURE_2D, GL_TEXTURE_MAG_FILTER, GL_LINEAR);
1846 glTexParameteri(GL_TEXTURE_2D, GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_S, wrap);
1847 glTexParameteri(GL_TEXTURE_2D, GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_T, wrap);
1848 glTexImage2D(GL_TEXTURE_2D, 0, GL_RGBA, w, h, 0, GL_RGBA, GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE, data);
1849#if defined(GL_UNPACK_ROW_LENGTH) && !defined(__EMSCRIPTEN__)
1850 glPixelStorei(GL_UNPACK_ROW_LENGTH, 0);
1851#endif
1852 glBindTexture(GL_TEXTURE_2D, 0);
1853
1854 return texture;
1855}
1856
1860GLuint
1861load_texture(char fname[200])
1862{
1863 int width, height;
1864 char fname2[200];
1865 sprintf(fname2, "%s%s", settings.assets_dir, fname);
1866 uint8_t* data = stbi_load(fname2, &width, &height, NULL, 4);
1867 if (!data) {
1868 return 0;
1869 }
1870
1871 GLuint texture_id = gen_gl_texture(data, width, height, GL_CLAMP_TO_EDGE);
1872 stbi_image_free(data);
1873
1874 return texture_id;
1875}

3922 p.y = -previewPoint.y;
3923 rot = embVector_rotate(p, alpha);
3924 rot = embVector_add(rot, previewPoint);
3925
3926 previewObjectItemGroup->setPos(rot);
3927 previewObjectItemGroup->setRotation(previewData - mouseAngle);
3928 }
3929 else if (previewMode == preview.MODE_SCALE) {
3930 EmbReal scaleFactor = previewData;
3931
3932 EmbReal factor = EmbLine(previewPoint, sceneMousePoint).length()/scaleFactor;
3933
3934 previewObjectItemGroup->setScale(1);
3935 previewObjectItemGroup->setPos(0,0);
3936
3937 if (scaleFactor <= 0.0) {
3938 critical_messagebox(translate("ScaleFactor Error"),
3939 translate("Hi there. If you are not a developer, report this as a bug. "
3940 "If you are a developer, your code needs examined, and possibly your head too."));
3941 }
3942 else {
3943 //Calculate the offset
3944 EmbVector old(0, 0);
3945 EmbLine scaleLine(preview.point, old);
3946 scaleLine.setLength(scaleLine.length()*factor);
3947
3948 EmbVector delta = embVector_subtract(scaleLine.end, old);
3949
3950 previewObjectItemGroup->setScale(previewObjectItemGroup->scale()*factor);
3951 previewObjectItemGroup->moveBy(delta);
3952 }
3953 }
3954 }
3955 if (active_view->pasting_active) {
3956 pasteObjectItemGroup->setPos(sceneMousePoint - pasteDelta);
3957 }
3958 if (movingActive) {
3959 //Ensure that the preview is only shown if the mouse has moved.
3960 if (!previewActive)
3961 previewOn(PREVIEW_CLONE_SELECTED, preview.MODE_MOVE, scenePressPoint.x, scenePressPoint.y, 0);
3962 }
3963 if (selectingActive) {
3964 if (sceneMovePoint.x >= scenePressPoint.x) {
3965 selectBox->setDirection(1);
3966 }
3967 else {
3968 selectBox->setDirection(0);
3969 }
3970 selectBox->setGeometry(EmbRect(map_from_scene(scenePressPoint), event->pos()).normalized());
3971 event->accept();
3972 }
3973 if (panningActive) {
3974 horizontalscrollbar()->setValue(horizontalscrollbar()->value() - (event->x - panStartX));
3975 verticalscrollbar()->setValue(verticalscrollbar()->value() - (event->y - panStartY));
3976 panStartX = event->x;
3977 panStartY = event->y;
3978 event->accept();
3979 }
3980 */
3981}

4908static void
4909property_editor(void)
4910{
4911 if (n_views == 0) {
4912 return;
4913 }
4914
4915 EmbPattern *pattern = views[settings.pattern_index].pattern;
4916
4917 char msg[200];
4918 sprintf(msg, "%s%s",
4919 translate("Property Editor"),
4920 views[settings.pattern_index].filename);
4921 begin_child(msg);
4922 translated_text("Properties");
4923 /*
4924 propertyEditorButtonStyle = ToolButtonTextBesideIcon; //\todo Make customizable
4925
4926 pickAdd = pickAddMode;
4927
4928 precisionAngle = 0;
4929 precisionLength = 4;
4930 */
4931
4932 if (pattern) {
4933 create_group_box_general(settings.pattern_index, pattern);
4934 }
4935
4936 for (int i=0; i<pattern->geometry->count; i++) {
4937 if (pattern->geometry->geometry[i].type == EMB_ARC) {
4938 EmbArc *arc = &(pattern->geometry->geometry[i].object.arc);
4939 create_group_box_arc(i, arc);
4940 }
4941 }
4942
4943 if (0) {
4944 create_group_box_block(0, NULL);
4945 }
4946
4947 for (int i=0; i<pattern->geometry->count; i++) {
4948 if (pattern->geometry->geometry[i].type == EMB_CIRCLE) {
4949 EmbCircle *circle = &(pattern->geometry->geometry[i].object.circle);
4950 create_group_box_circle(i, circle);
4951 }
4952 }
4953
4954 if (0) {
4955 create_group_box_dim_aligned(0, NULL);
4956 }
4957
4958 if (0) {
4959 create_group_box_dim_angular(0, NULL);
4960 }
4961
4962 if (0) {
4963 create_group_box_dim_arc_length(0, NULL);
4964 }
4965
4966 if (0) {
4967 create_group_box_dim_diameter(0, NULL);
4968 }
4969
4970 if (0) {
4971 create_group_box_dim_leader(0, NULL);
4972 }
4973
4974 if (0) {
4975 create_group_box_dim_linear(0, NULL);
4976 }
4977
4978 if (0) {
4979 create_group_box_dim_ordinate(0, NULL);
4980 }
4981
4982 if (0) {
4983 create_group_box_dim_radius(0, NULL);
4984 }
4985
4986 for (int i=0; i<pattern->geometry->count; i++) {
4987 if (pattern->geometry->geometry[i].type == EMB_ELLIPSE) {
4988 EmbEllipse *ellipse = &(pattern->geometry->geometry[i].object.ellipse);
4989 create_group_box_ellipse(i, ellipse);
4990 }
4991 }
4992
4993 if (0) {
4994 create_group_box_image(0, NULL);
4995 }
4996
4997 if (0) {
4998 create_group_box_infinite_line(0, NULL);
4999 }
5000
5001 for (int i=0; i<pattern->geometry->count; i++) {
5002 if (pattern->geometry->geometry[i].type == EMB_LINE) {
5003 EmbLine *line = &(pattern->geometry->geometry[i].object.line);
5004 create_group_box_line(i, line);
5005 }
5006 }
5007
5008 for (int i=0; i<pattern->geometry->count; i++) {
5009 if (pattern->geometry->geometry[i].type == EMB_PATH) {
5010 EmbPath *path = &(pattern->geometry->geometry[i].object.path);
5011 create_group_box_path(i, path);
5012 }
5013 }
5014
5015 for (int i=0; i<pattern->geometry->count; i++) {
5016 if (pattern->geometry->geometry[i].type == EMB_POINT) {
5017 EmbPoint *point = &(pattern->geometry->geometry[i].object.point);
5018 create_group_box_point(i, point);
5019 }
5020 }
5021
5022 for (int i=0; i<pattern->geometry->count; i++) {
5023 if (pattern->geometry->geometry[i].type == EMB_POLYGON) {
5024 EmbPolygon *polygon = &(pattern->geometry->geometry[i].object.polygon);
5025 create_group_box_polygon(i, polygon);
5026 }
5027 }
5028
5029 for (int i=0; i<pattern->geometry->count; i++) {
5030 if (pattern->geometry->geometry[i].type == EMB_POLYLINE) {
5031 EmbPolyline *polyline = &(pattern->geometry->geometry[i].object.polyline);
5032 create_group_box_polyline(i, polyline);
5033 }
5034 }
5035
5036 if (0) {
5037 create_group_box_ray(0, NULL);
5038 }
5039
5040 for (int i=0; i<pattern->geometry->count; i++) {
5041 if (pattern->geometry->geometry[i].type == EMB_RECT) {
5042 EmbRect *rect = &(pattern->geometry->geometry[i].object.rect);
5043 create_group_box_rectangle(i, rect);
5044 }
5045 }
5046
5047 if (pattern->stitch_list->count > 0) {
5048 create_group_box_stitch_list(settings.pattern_index, pattern->stitch_list);
5049 }
5050
5051 if (0) {
5052 create_group_box_text_multi(0, NULL);
5053 }
5054
5055 if (0) {
5056 create_group_box_text_single(0, NULL);
5057 }
5058
5059 end_child();
5060}

6281
6285static bool stor[10];
6286
6291static void
6292create_group_box_stitch(int i, EmbStitch *st)
6293{
6294 char decorator[200], label[200];
6295 sprintf(decorator, "##stitch%d %d", settings.pattern_index, i);
6296 sprintf(label, "Stitch %d%s", i, decorator);
6297 if (i == 0) {
6298 sprintf(label, "Home%s", decorator);
6299 }
6300 if (collapsing_header(label)) {
6301 char s[200];
6302 sprintf(s, "X%s", decorator);
6303 edit_real(s, &(st->x));
6304 sprintf(s, "Y%s", decorator);
6305 edit_real(s, &(st->y));
6306 /* \todo checkboxes for individual flags */
6307 translated_text("Flags");
6308
6309 /* The stors need to be distinct memory locations. */
6310 stor[0] = st->flags & TRIM;
6311 sprintf(s, "TRIM%s", decorator);
6312 checkbox_data(s, stor, stor);
6313
6314 stor[1] = st->flags & NORMAL;
6315 sprintf(s, "NORMAL%s", decorator);
6316 checkbox_data(s, stor+1, stor+1);
6317
6318 stor[2] = st->flags & END;
6319 sprintf(s, "END%s", decorator);
6320 checkbox_data(s, stor+2, stor+2);
6321
6322 st->flags = (stor[0] & TRIM) + (stor[1] & NORMAL) + (stor[2] & END);
6323
6324 sprintf(s, "Thread Index%s", decorator);
6325 edit_int(s, &(st->color));
6326 }
6327}
6328
6332static int from_ = 0;
6333static int to_ = 10;
6334
6339static void
6340create_group_box_stitch_list(int id, EmbArray *stitch_list)
6341{
6342 char label[200];
6343 sprintf(label, "%s ID:%d", translate("Stitch List"), id+1);
6344 if (collapsing_header(label)) {
6345 char s[200];
6346 sprintf(s, "From##%d", id+1);
6347 edit_int(s, &from_);
6348 sprintf(s, "To##%d", id+1);
6349 edit_int(s, &to_);
6350 if (to_ < from_) {
6351 to_ = from_;
6352 }
6353 if (to_ > stitch_list->count) {
6354 to_ = stitch_list->count;
6355 }
6356 for (int i=from_; i<to_; i++) {
6357 EmbStitch *st = &(stitch_list->stitch[i]);
6358 create_group_box_stitch(i, st);
6359 }
6360 }
6361}

6423
6429Index *index_init(void)
6430{
6431 Index *index = (Index*)malloc(sizeof(Index));
6432 index->max_length = 1000;
6433 index->length = 0;
6434 index->data = (IndexEntry*)malloc(1000*sizeof(IndexEntry));
6435 return index;
6436}
6437
6441static void
6442index_free(Index *index)
6443{
6444 free(index->data);
6445 free(index);
6446}
6447
6451Dictionary *
6452dictionary_from_index(Index *index, const char *label)
6453{
6454 for (int i=0; i<index->length; i++) {
6455 if (!strcmp(index->data[i].key, label)) {
6456 return index->data[i].value;
6457 }
6458 }
6459 return NULL;
6460}
6461
6467UndoHistory
6468undo_history_init(void)
6469{
6470 UndoHistory undo_history;
6471 undo_history.max_length = 100;
6472 undo_history.length = 0;
6473 undo_history.position = 0;
6474 return undo_history;
6475}
6476
6480static void
6481add_to_undo_history(UndoHistory *undo_history, const char *command_line)
6482{
6483 int pos = undo_history->position;
6484 strcpy(undo_history->data[pos], command_line);
6485 undo_history->position++;
6486 undo_history->length++;
6487 if (undo_history->position >= 80) {
6488 for (int i=0; i<80; i++) {
6489 strcpy(undo_history->data[i], undo_history->data[i+20]);
6490 }
6491 undo_history->position -= 20;
6492 undo_history->length -= 20;
6493 }
6494}
6495
6499static void
6500load_configuration(void)
6501{
6502 char error_buffer[200];
6503 FILE *f;
6504 char fname[200];
6505 sprintf(fname, "%sem2_config.toml", settings.assets_dir);
6506 f = fopen(fname, "r");
6507 if (!f) {
6508 log_debug("ERROR: failed to open configuration file \"em2_config.toml\".");
6509 settings.running = false;
6510 return;
6511 }
6512 toml_table_t *config = toml_parse_file(f, error_buffer, sizeof(error_buffer));
6513 fclose(f);
6514
6515 if (!config) {
6516 log_debug("ERROR: failed to parse \"em2_config.toml\".");
6517 settings.running = false;
6518 return;
6519 }
6520
6521 Dictionary *menu = read_dictionary_setting(config, "menu_layout");
6522 char cmd[200];
6523 sprintf(cmd, "menu length: %d", menu->length);
6524 log_debug(cmd);
6525 menu_layout = index_init();
6526 for (int i=0; i<menu->length; i++) {
6527 strcpy(menu_layout->data[i].key, menu->data[i].key);
6528 menu_layout->data[i].value = read_dictionary_setting(config, menu->data[i].value);
6529 menu_layout->length++;
6530 }
6531
6532 Dictionary *toolbar = read_dictionary_setting(config, "toolbar_layout");
6533 sprintf(cmd, "toolbar length: %d", toolbar->length);
6534 log_debug(cmd);
6535 toolbar_layout = index_init();
6536 for (int i=0; i<toolbar->length; i++) {
6537 strcpy(toolbar_layout->data[i].key, toolbar->data[i].key);
6538 toolbar_layout->data[i].value = read_dictionary_setting(config, toolbar->data[i].value);
6539 toolbar_layout->length++;
6540 }
6541
6542 /* string_matrix actions = load_string_matrix(config, "action_list"); */
6543
6544 settings.texture_list = read_dictionary_setting(config, "texture_list");
6545 sprintf(cmd, "texture_list length: %d", settings.texture_list->length);
6546 log_debug(cmd);
6547
6548 read_str_setting(config, "version", settings.version);
6549 log_debug(settings.version);
6550 toml_free(config);
6551}
6552
6556static void
6557read_str_setting(toml_table_t *table, const char *key, char s[200])
6558{
6559 toml_datum_t result_in = toml_string_in(table, key);
6560 if (result_in.ok) {
6561 strcpy(s, result_in.u.s);
6562 }
6563 else {
6564 char error[200];
6565 sprintf(error, "ERROR: failed to read %s.\n", key);
6566 log_debug(error);
6567 }
6568 free(result_in.u.s);
6569}
6570
6574int
6575read_int_setting(toml_table_t *table, const char *key)
6576{
6577 toml_datum_t result_in = toml_int_in(table, key);
6578 if (!result_in.ok) {
6579 char s[200];
6580 sprintf(s, "ERROR: failed to read %s.\n", key);
6581 log_debug(s);
6582 return 0;
6583 }
6584 return result_in.u.i;
6585}
6586
6590bool
6591read_bool_setting(toml_table_t *table, const char *key)
6592{
6593 toml_datum_t result_in = toml_bool_in(table, key);
6594 if (!result_in.ok) {
6595 char s[200];
6596 sprintf(s, "ERROR: failed to read %s.\n", key);
6597 log_debug(s);
6598 }
6599 return result_in.u.b;
6600}
6601
6605Dictionary *
6606read_dictionary_setting(toml_table_t *table, const char *key)
6607{
6608 Dictionary *dict = (Dictionary*)malloc(sizeof(Dictionary));
6609 dict->data = (DictionaryEntry*)malloc(200*sizeof(DictionaryEntry));
6610 dict->length = 0;
6611 dict->max_length = 200;
6612 toml_array_t *array = toml_array_in(table, key);
6613
6614 if (!array) {
6615 char s[200];
6616 sprintf(s, "ERROR: failed to read %s.\n", key);
6617 log_debug(s);
6618 return NULL;
6619 }
6620
6621 for (int i=0; ; i++) {
6622 toml_datum_t str1;
6623 dict->length = i;
6624 toml_array_t *a2 = toml_array_at(array, i);
6625 if (!a2) {
6626 break;
6627 }
6628 str1 = toml_string_at(a2, 0);
6629 if (!str1.ok) {
6630 free(str1.u.s);
6631 break;
6632 }
6633 strcpy(dict->data[i].key, str1.u.s);
6634
6635 str1 = toml_string_at(a2, 1);
6636 if (!str1.ok) {
6637 free(str1.u.s);
6638 break;
6639 }
6640 strcpy(dict->data[i].value, str1.u.s);
6641 free(str1.u.s);
6642 }
6643
6644 return dict;
6645}
6646
6650static void
6651write_float_setting(FILE *file, const char *key, float value)
6652{
6653 fprintf(file, "%s = %f\n", key, value);
6654}
6655
6659static void
6660write_int_setting(FILE *file, const char *key, int value)
6661{
6662 fprintf(file, "%s = %d\n", key, value);
6663}
6664
6668static void
6669write_uint_setting(FILE *file, const char *key, unsigned int value)
6670{
6671 fprintf(file, "%s = %u\n", key, value);
6672}
6673
6677static void
6678write_str_setting(FILE *file, const char *key, const char value[200])
6679{
6680 fprintf(file, "%s = \"%s\"\n", key, value);
6681}
6682
6686static void
6687write_bool_setting(FILE *file, const char *key, bool value)
6688{
6689 if (value) {
6690 fprintf(file, "%s = true\n", key);
6691 }
6692 else {
6693 fprintf(file, "%s = false\n", key);
6694 }
6695}
6696
6700static void
6701write_dictionary_setting(FILE *file, const char *key, Dictionary dict)
6702{
6703 fprintf(file, "%s = [\n", key);
6704 for (int i=0; i<dict.length-1; i++) {
6705 fprintf(file, " [%s, %s],\n", dict.data[i].key, dict.data[i].value);
6706 }
6707 fprintf(file, " [%s, %s]\n",
6708 dict.data[dict.length-1].key,
6709 dict.data[dict.length-1].value);
6710 fprintf(file, "]\n\n");
6711}

6988 write_bool_setting(file, "Parallel", settings.qsnap_parallel);
6989 fprintf(file, "\n");
6990
6991 fprintf(file, "[LineWeight]\n");
6992 write_bool_setting(file, "ShowLineWeight", settings.lwt_show_lwt);
6993 write_bool_setting(file, "RealRender", settings.lwt_real_render);
6994 write_bool_setting(file, "DefaultLineWeight", settings.lwt_default_lwt);
6995 fprintf(file, "\n");
6996
6997 fprintf(file, "[Selection]\n");
6998 write_bool_setting(file, "PickFirst", settings.selection_mode_pickfirst);
6999 write_bool_setting(file, "PickAdd", settings.selection_mode_pickadd);
7000 write_bool_setting(file, "PickDrag", settings.selection_mode_pickdrag);
7001 write_bool_setting(file, "CoolGripColor", settings.selection_coolgrip_color);
7002 write_bool_setting(file, "HotGripColor", settings.selection_hotgrip_color);
7003 write_bool_setting(file, "GripSize", settings.selection_grip_size);
7004 write_bool_setting(file, "PickBoxSize", settings.selection_pickbox_size);
7005 fprintf(file, "\n");
7006
7007 fprintf(file, "[Text]\n");
7008 write_str_setting(file, "Font", settings.text_font);
7009 write_int_setting(file, "Size", settings.text_size);
7010 write_float_setting(file, "Angle", settings.text_angle);
7011 write_bool_setting(file, "StyleBold", settings.text_style_bold);
7012 write_bool_setting(file, "StyleItalic", settings.text_style_italic);
7013 write_bool_setting(file, "StyleUnderline", settings.text_style_underline);
7014 write_bool_setting(file, "StyleStrikeOut", settings.text_style_strikeout);
7015 write_bool_setting(file, "StyleOverline", settings.text_style_overline);
7016 fclose(file);
7017}

7023static void
7024platform_string(char str[200])
7025{
7026 strcpy(str, "Unknown plaform.");
7027 #if _WIN32
7028 strcpy(str, "Windows");
7029 #endif
7030 #ifdef __linux__
7031 struct utsname buffer;
7032 uname(&buffer);
7033 sprintf(str, "%s %s %s %s %s",
7034 buffer.sysname,
7035 buffer.nodename,
7036 buffer.release,
7037 buffer.version,
7038 buffer.machine);
7039 #endif
7040}

7078void
7079log_debug(const char *msg)
7080{

7087
7091bool
7092validRGB(int r, int g, int b)
7093{
7094 if (r < 0 || r > 255) {
7095 log_debug("ERROR: r value must be in range 0-255");
7096 return false;
7097 }
7098 if (g < 0 || g > 255) {
7099 log_debug("ERROR: g value must be in range 0-255");
7100 return false;
7101 }
7102 if (b < 0 || b > 255) {
7103 log_debug("ERROR: b value must be in range 0-255");
7104 return 0;
7105 }
7106 return true;
7107}
7108
7118bool
7119streq(const char *s1, const char *s2)
7120{
7121 return !strncmp(s1, s2, 200);
7122}
7123
7132const char *
7133translate(const char *string)
7134{
7135 if (settings.use_translation) {
7136 return string;
7137 }
7138 return string;
7139 for (int i=0; i<translation_table->length; i++) {
7140 if (streq(translation_table->data[i].key, string)) {
7141 return translation_table->data[i].value;
7142 }
7143 }
7144 return string;
7145}

7152int
7153render_pattern(EmbPattern *p)
7154{
7155 for (int i=0; i<p->geometry->count; i++) {
7156 EmbGeometry g = p->geometry->geometry[i];
7157 int color = embColor_to_int(g.color, 255);
7158 switch (g.type) {
7159 case EMB_CIRCLE: {
7160 EmbCircle c = g.object.circle;
7161 EmbVector scene_center = embVector_add(c.center, active_view->origin);
7162 EmbReal scene_radius = c.radius * active_view->scale;
7163 draw_circle(scene_center, scene_radius, color, false);
7164 // \todo fill
7165 break;
7166 }
7167 case EMB_ELLIPSE: {
7168 /*
7169 EmbEllipse e = g.object.ellipse;
7170 int color = embColor_to_int(e.color);
7171 //draw_list->AddEllipse(e.center.x, e.center.y, e.radius.x, e.radius.y, color);
7172 */
7173 break;
7174 }
7175 case EMB_LINE: {
7176 EmbVector scene_start, scene_end;
7177 EmbLine li = g.object.line;
7178 scene_start = embVector_add(li.start, active_view->origin);
7179 scene_end = embVector_add(li.end, active_view->origin);
7180 draw_line(scene_start, scene_end, color);
7181 break;
7182 }
7183 case EMB_PATH: {
7184 /*
7185 for (int i=0; i<p->paths->count; i++) {
7186 EmbPath path;
7187 EmbArray *curPointList = path.pointList;
7188 if (curPointList) {
7189 EmbPoint pp = curPointList->point[0];
7190 pathPath.moveTo(pp.position.x, -pp.position.y);
7191 //NOTE: Qt Y+ is down and libembroidery Y+ is up, so inverting the Y is needed.
7192 }
7193 for (int j=0; j<curPointList->count; j++) {
7194 EmbPoint pp = curPointList->point[j];
7195 pathPath.lineTo(pp.position.x, -pp.position.y);
7196 // NOTE: Qt Y+ is down and libembroidery Y+ is up, so inverting the Y is needed.
7197 }
7198
7199 QPen loadPen(qRgb(thisColor.r, thisColor.g, thisColor.b));
7200 loadPen.setWidthF(0.35);
7201 loadPen.setCapStyle(RoundCap);
7202 loadPen.setJoinStyle(RoundJoin);
7203
7204 PathObject* obj = PathObject(0,0, pathPath, loadPen.color().rgb());
7205 obj->setObjectRubberMode(OBJ_RUBBER_OFF);
7206 active_view->addItem(obj);
7207 }
7208 */
7209 break;
7210 }
7211 case EMB_POINT: {
7212 EmbPoint po = g.object.point;
7213 EmbReal point_size = 10.0;
7214 draw_circle(po.position, point_size, color, false);
7215 break;
7216 }
7217 case EMB_POLYGON: {
7218 /*
7219 for (int i=0; i<p->polygons->count; i++) {
7220 // EmbPath polygonPath;
7221 EmbPolygon polygon = p->polygons->polygon[i];
7222 bool firstPoint = false;
7223 EmbVector start = {0.0, 0.0};
7224 EmbReal x = 0.0, y = 0.0;
7225 EmbArray *curPointList = polygon.pointList;
7226 for (int j=0; j<curPointList->count; j++) {
7227 EmbPoint pp = curPointList->point[j];
7228 x = pp.position.x;
7229 y = -pp.position.y;
7230
7231 if (firstPoint) {
7232 polygonPath.lineTo(x,y);
7233 }
7234 else {
7235 polygonPath.moveTo(x,y);
7236 firstPoint = true;
7237 startX = x;
7238 startY = y;
7239 }
7240 }
7241
7242 polygonPath.translate(-startX, -startY);
7243 AddPolygon(startX, startY, polygonPath, OBJ_RUBBER_OFF);
7244 }
7245 */
7246 break;
7247 }
7248 /* NOTE: Polylines should only contain NORMAL stitches. */
7249 case EMB_POLYLINE: {
7250 EmbPolyline pl = g.object.polyline;
7251 EmbArray *curPointList = pl.pointList;
7252 EmbLine line;
7253 line.start = curPointList->geometry[0].object.point.position;
7254 for (int j=1; j<curPointList->count; j++) {
7255 EmbPoint pp = curPointList->geometry[j].object.point;
7256 line.end.x = pp.position.x;
7257 line.end.y = -pp.position.y;
7258 draw_line(line.start, line.end, color);
7259 }
7260
7261 /*
7262 polylinePath.translate(-startX, -startY);
7263 addPolyline(startX, startY, polylinePath, OBJ_RUBBER_OFF);
7264 */
7265 break;
7266 }
7267 case EMB_RECT: {
7268 /*
7269 EmbRect r = p->rects->rect[i];
7270 EmbVector position1 = {(float)r.left, (float)r.top};
7271 EmbVector position2 = {(float)r.right, (float)r.bottom};
7272 draw_rect(position1, position2, color); //\todo rotation and fill
7273 */
7274 break;
7275 }
7276 default:
7277 break;
7278 }
7279 }
7280 if (p->stitch_list->count > 1) {
7281 for (int i = 1; i<p->stitch_list->count; i++) {
7282 EmbStitch prev = p->stitch_list->stitch[i-1];
7283 EmbStitch st = p->stitch_list->stitch[i];
7284 EmbLine line = stitch_line_to_scene(*active_view, prev, st);
7285 EmbThread thread = p->thread_list->thread[st.color];
7286 int color = embColor_to_int(thread.color, 255);
7287 draw_line(line.start, line.end, color);
7288 }
7289 }
7290 return 0;
7291}
7292
7299static void
7300render_shine(EmbVector start, EmbVector end, EmbVector normal, float start_frac, float end_frac)
7301{
7302 EmbVector delta, shine_start, shine_end, corner1, corner2, corner3, corner4;
7303 delta = embVector_subtract(end, start);
7304 shine_start = start;
7305 shine_end = end;
7306 shine_start.x += start_frac*delta.x;
7307 shine_start.y += start_frac*delta.y;
7308 shine_end.x += end_frac*delta.x;
7309 shine_end.y += end_frac*delta.y;
7310
7311 corner1 = embVector_add(shine_start, normal);
7312 corner2 = embVector_subtract(shine_start, normal);
7313 corner3 = embVector_subtract(shine_end, normal);
7314 corner4 = embVector_add(shine_end, normal);
7315
7316 draw_quad(corner1, corner2, corner3, corner4, settings.shine_color);
7317}
7318
7322EmbLine
7323stitch_line_to_scene(View view, EmbStitch prev, EmbStitch st)
7324{
7325 EmbVector offset = get_window_pos();
7326 EmbLine line;
7327 line.start.x = view.scale*prev.x;
7328 line.start.y = -view.scale*prev.y;
7329 line.end.x = view.scale*st.x;
7330 line.end.y = -view.scale*st.y;
7331 offset = embVector_add(offset, view.origin);
7332 line.start = embVector_add(line.start, offset);
7333 line.end = embVector_add(line.end, offset);
7334 return line;
7335}
7336
7340static void
7341real_render_pattern(EmbPattern *p)
7342{
7343 if (p->stitch_list->count > 1) {
7344 for (int i = 1; i<p->stitch_list->count; i++) {
7345 EmbStitch prev = p->stitch_list->stitch[i-1];
7346 EmbStitch st = p->stitch_list->stitch[i];
7347 EmbLine line = stitch_line_to_scene(*active_view, prev, st);
7348
7349 float lwt = 2.0;
7350 EmbVector delta;
7351 delta.x = prev.y - st.y;
7352 delta.y = prev.x - st.x;
7353 EmbVector normal_;
7354 embVector_normalize(delta, &normal_);
7355 normal_.x *= lwt;
7356 normal_.y *= lwt;
7357
7358 EmbThread thread = p->thread_list->thread[st.color];
7359 int color = embColor_to_int(thread.color, 255);
7360 EmbVector corner1, corner2, corner3, corner4;
7361 corner1 = embVector_add(line.start, normal_);
7362 corner2 = embVector_subtract(line.start, normal_);
7363 corner3 = embVector_subtract(line.end, normal_);
7364 corner4 = embVector_add(line.end, normal_);
7365 draw_quad(corner1, corner2, corner3, corner4, color);
7366 render_shine(line.start, line.end, normal_, 0.333*0.3, 0.333*0.7);
7367 render_shine(line.start, line.end, normal_, 0.333*0.1, 0.333*0.9);
7368 render_shine(line.start, line.end, normal_, 0.333*1.3, 0.333*1.7);
7369 render_shine(line.start, line.end, normal_, 0.333*1.1, 0.333*1.9);
7370 render_shine(line.start, line.end, normal_, 0.333*2.3, 0.333*2.7);
7371 render_shine(line.start, line.end, normal_, 0.333*2.1, 0.333*2.9);
7372 }
7373 }
7374}
7375
7379static void
7380simulate_pattern(EmbPattern *p)
7381{
7382 clock_t duration = clock() - active_view->simulation_start;
7383 float time_passed = duration / (1.0 * CLOCKS_PER_SEC);
7384 int stitches = 0;
7385 if (p->stitch_list->count > 1) {
7386 float current_time = 0.0;
7387 for (int i = 1; i<p->stitch_list->count; i++) {
7388 EmbStitch prev = p->stitch_list->stitch[i-1];
7389 EmbStitch st = p->stitch_list->stitch[i];
7390 EmbLine line = stitch_line_to_scene(*active_view, prev, st);
7391
7392 EmbThread thread = p->thread_list->thread[st.color];
7393 int color = embColor_to_int(thread.color, 255);
7394 EmbVector delta = {prev.x-st.x, prev.y-st.y};
7395 float time_for_stitch = settings.stitch_time
7396 + embVector_length(delta)/settings.needle_speed;
7397 current_time += time_for_stitch;
7398 stitches = i;
7399 if (current_time > time_passed) {
7400 float t = current_time-time_passed-time_for_stitch;
7401 EmbVector scene_delta;
7402 scene_delta = embVector_subtract(line.end, line.start);
7403 line.end.x = line.start.x - t*scene_delta.x;
7404 line.end.y = line.start.y - t*scene_delta.y;
7405 draw_line(line.start, line.end, color);
7406 break;
7407 }
7408 else {
7409 draw_line(line.start, line.end, color);
7410 }
7411 }
7412 }
7413
7414 begin_ui("Controls", 500, 500);
7415 char s[200];
7416 sprintf(s, "Stitch: %d/%d", stitches, p->stitch_list->count);
7417 translated_text(s);
7418 show_real("Needle Speed: ", settings.needle_speed);
7419 show_real("Stitch Time: ", settings.stitch_time);
7420 show_real("Time Passed: ", time_passed);
7421
7422 if (button("Slower")) {
7423 settings.needle_speed /= 2.0;
7424 settings.stitch_time *= 2.0;
7425 }
7426 same_line();
7427 if (button("Faster")) {
7428 settings.needle_speed *= 2.0;
7429 settings.stitch_time /= 2.0;
7430 }
7431
7432 if (button("Start")) {
7433 active_view->simulation_start = clock();
7434 }
7435 same_line();
7436 if (button("Previous Stitch")) {
7437
7438 }
7439 same_line();
7440 if (button("Next Stitch")) {
7441
7442 }
7443 same_line();
7444 if (button("End")) {
7445
7446 }
7447
7448 if (button("Close")) {
7449 active_view->simulate = false;
7450 }
7451 end_ui();
7452}

7459static void
7460draw_rulers(void)
7461{
7462 EmbVector offset = get_window_pos();
7463 EmbVector screen_size = get_screen_size();
7464 EmbVector dimensions;
7465 dimensions.x = offset.x + settings.ruler_width;
7466 dimensions.y = offset.y + screen_size.y;
7467 draw_rect(offset, dimensions, settings.ruler_color, true);
7468 dimensions.x = offset.x + screen_size.x;
7469 dimensions.y = offset.y + settings.ruler_width;
7470 draw_rect(offset, dimensions, settings.ruler_color, true);
7471 EmbVector origin_x, origin_y;
7472 origin_x.x = active_view->origin.x;
7473 origin_x.y = 0.0;
7474 origin_y.x = 0.0;
7475 origin_y.y = active_view->origin.y;
7476 float major_tick_seperation_scaled = active_view->scale * settings.major_tick_seperation;
7477 if (active_view->metric) {
7478 int repeats = 100;
7479 for (int i=-repeats; i<repeats; i++) {
7480 float ruler_pos = settings.ruler_width
7481 + major_tick_seperation_scaled*i;
7482 EmbLine line;
7483 line.start.x = offset.x + origin_x.x + ruler_pos;
7484 line.start.y = offset.y + origin_x.y;
7485 line.end.x = offset.x + origin_x.x + ruler_pos;
7486 line.end.y = offset.y + origin_x.y + settings.ruler_width;
7487 draw_line(line.start, line.end, settings.ticks_color);
7488 char label[200];
7489 sprintf(label, "%d", i);
7490 line.start.x += 5.0;
7491 draw_text(line.start, settings.ticks_color, label);
7492 for (int j=0; j<10; j++) {
7493 ruler_pos += major_tick_seperation_scaled/10.0;
7494 EmbLine tick;
7495 tick.start.x = offset.x + origin_x.x + ruler_pos;
7496 tick.start.y = offset.y + origin_x.y + settings.tick_depth;
7497 tick.end.x = offset.x + origin_x.x + ruler_pos;
7498 tick.end.y = offset.y + origin_x.y + settings.ruler_width;

7510 char label[200];

7514 for (int j=0; j<10; j++) {
7515 ruler_pos += major_tick_seperation_scaled/10.0;
7516 EmbLine tick;
7517 tick.start.x = offset.x + origin_y.x + settings.tick_depth;

7519 tick.end.x = offset.x + origin_y.x + settings.ruler_width;
7520 tick.end.y = offset.y + origin_y.y + ruler_pos;
7521 draw_line(tick.start, tick.end, settings.ticks_color);
7522 }
7523 }
7524 }
7525 else {
7526 /*
7527 int repeats = 100;
7528 for (int i=0; i<repeats; i++) {
7529 float ruler_pos = settings.ruler_width + settings.major_tick_seperation*i;

7578
7582static void
7583draw_grid(void)
7584{
7585 EmbVector offset = get_window_pos();
7586 EmbVector screen_size = get_screen_size();
7587 for (float x=offset.x; x<screen_size.x; x+=settings.grid_spacing.x) {
7588 EmbVector start, end;
7589 start.x = x;
7590 start.y = offset.y;
7591 end.x = x;
7592 end.y = screen_size.y;
7593 draw_line(start, end, settings.grid_color);
7594 }
7595 for (float y=offset.y; y<screen_size.y; y+=settings.grid_spacing.y) {
7596 EmbVector start, end;
7597 start.x = offset.x;
7598 start.y = y;
7599 end.x = screen_size.x;
7600 end.y = y;
7601 draw_line(start, end, settings.grid_color);
7602 }
7603}
7604
7608static void
7609pattern_view(void)
7610{
7611 EmbPattern *pattern = views[settings.pattern_index].pattern;
7612 begin_child(views[settings.pattern_index].filename);
7613 if (views[settings.pattern_index].grid_mode) {
7614 draw_grid();
7615 }
7616 if (views[settings.pattern_index].lwt_mode) {
7617 real_render_pattern(pattern);
7618 }
7619 else {
7620 if (views[settings.pattern_index].simulate) {
7621 simulate_pattern(pattern);
7622 }
7623 else {
7624 render_pattern(pattern);
7625 }
7626 }
7627 if (views[settings.pattern_index].ruler_mode) {
7628 draw_rulers();
7629 }
7630 end_child();
7631}
7632
7650View
7651init_view(void)
7652{
7653 /*
7654 (const int theIndex, MainWindow* mw, QMdiArea* parent, int wflags)
7655
7656 fileWasLoaded = false;
7657
7658 setAttribute(Qt_WA_DeleteOnClose);
7659
7660 this->setWindowIcon(load_icon("app"));
7661
7662 active_view = QGraphicsScene(0, 0, 0, 0, this);
7663 gview = View(mainWin, active_view, this);
7664
7665 setWidget(gview);
7666
7667 gview->setFocusProxy(prompt);
7668
7669 resize(sizeHint());
7670
7671 promptHistory = "Welcome to Embroidermodder 2!<br/>Open some of our sample files. Many formats are supported.<br/>For help, press F1.";
7672 prompt->setHistory(promptHistory);
7673 promptInputList << "";
7674 promptInputNum = 0;
7675
7676 curLayer = "0";
7677 curColor = 0; //\todo color ByLayer
7678 curLineType = "ByLayer";
7679 curLineWeight = "ByLayer";
7680
7681 show();
7682 showMaximized();
7683
7684 setFocusPolicy(Qt_WheelFocus);
7685 setFocus();
7686
7687 onWindowActivated();
7688
7689 view.useLogo = false;
7690 view.useTexture = false;
7691 view.useColor = false;
7692 view.bgLogo = "";
7693 view.bgTexture = "";
7694 view.bgColor = IM_COL32(40, 20, 10, 255);
7695 */
7696 View view;
7697 view.origin.x = 400.0;
7698 view.origin.y = 300.0;
7699 view.scale = 5.0;
7700 strcpy(view.grid_type, "RECTANGULAR");
7701 view.snap_mode = true;
7702 view.grid_mode = true;
7703 view.ruler_mode = true;
7704 view.ortho_mode = false;
7705 view.polar_mode = false;
7706 view.qsnap_mode = false;
7707 view.qtrack_mode = false;
7708 view.lwt_mode = false;
7709 view.metric = true;
7710 view.simulate = false;
7711 view.simulation_start = clock();
7712 strcpy(view.text_font, "default");
7713 view.text_size = 16;
7714 view.text_angle = 0.0;
7715 view.text_style_bold = false;
7716 view.text_style_italic = false;
7717 view.text_style_underline = false;
7718 view.text_style_overline = false;
7719 view.text_style_strikeout = false;
7720 if (n_views > 0) {
7721 sprintf(view.filename, "Untitled%02d.dst", n_views);
7722 }
7723 else {
7724 strcpy(view.filename, "Untitled.dst");
7725 }
7726 view.undo_history.position = 0;
7727 view.undo_history.length = 0;
7728 view.undo_history.max_length = 100;
7729 view.pattern = embPattern_create();
7730 view.rubber_mode = OBJ_RUBBER_OFF;
7731
7732 return view;
7733}

7738static void
7739settings_editor(void)
7740{
7741 if (just_opened) {
7742 dialog = settings;
7743 preview = dialog;
7744 just_opened = false;
7745 }
7746 // ImGuiTabItemFlags_SetSelected
7747 begin_ui("Settings", 750, 550);
7748 if (begin_tab_bar("Tab Bar")) {
7749 if (begin_tab_item("General")) {
7750 create_tab_general();
7751 end_tab_item();
7752 }
7753 if (begin_tab_item("Files/Paths")) {
7754 create_tab_files_paths();
7755 end_tab_item();
7756 }
7757 if (begin_tab_item("Display")) {
7758 create_tab_display();
7759 end_tab_item();
7760 }
7761 if (begin_tab_item("Open/Save")) {
7762 create_tab_open_save();
7763 end_tab_item();
7764 }
7765 if (begin_tab_item("Printing")) {
7766 create_tab_printing();
7767 end_tab_item();
7768 }
7769 if (begin_tab_item("Snap")) {
7770 create_tab_snap();
7771 end_tab_item();
7772 }
7773 if (begin_tab_item("Grid/Ruler")) {
7774 create_tab_grid_ruler();
7775 end_tab_item();
7776 }
7777 if (begin_tab_item("Ortho/Polar")) {
7778 create_tab_ortho_polar();
7779 end_tab_item();
7780 }
7781 if (begin_tab_item("QuickSnap")) {
7782 create_tab_quicksnap();
7783 end_tab_item();
7784 }
7785 if (begin_tab_item("QuickTrack")) {
7786 create_tab_quicktrack();
7787 end_tab_item();
7788 }
7789 if (begin_tab_item("LineWeight")) {
7790 create_tab_lineweight();
7791 end_tab_item();
7792 }
7793 if (begin_tab_item("Selection")) {
7794 create_tab_selection();
7795 end_tab_item();
7796 }
7797 end_tab_bar();
7798 }
7799
7800 if (button("Accept")) {
7801 log_debug("Writing Settings...");
7802 write_settings(settings_file);
7803 settings = dialog;
7804 settings.show_settings_editor = false;
7805 }
7806 same_line();
7807 if (button("Cancel")) {
7808 settings.show_settings_editor = false;
7809 }
7810 end_ui();
7811}

8150static void
8151create_tab_open_save(void)
8152{
8153 char extensions[100][20] = {
8154 "100", "10o", "ART", "BMC", "BRO", "CND", "COL", "CSD",
8155 "CSV", "DAT", "DEM", "DSB", "DST", "DSZ", "DXF", "EDR",
8156 "EMD", "EXP", "EXY", "EYS", "FXY", "GNC", "GT", "HUS",
8157 "INB", "JEF", "KSM", "PCD", "PCM", "PCQ", "PCS", "PEC",
8158 "PEL", "PEM", "PES", "PHB", "PHC", "RGB", "SEW", "SHV",
8159 "SST", "STX", "SVG", "T09", "TAP", "THR", "TXT",
8160 "U00", "U01", "VIP", "VP3", "XXX", "ZSK"
8161 };
8162
8163 printf("%s", extensions[100]);
8164
8165 /*
8166 //Custom Filter
8167 QGroupBox* groupBoxCustomFilter = QGroupBox(translate("Custom Filter"), widget);
8168 groupBoxCustomFilter->setEnabled(false); //\todo Fixup custom filter
8169
8170 dialog.opensave_custom_filter = settings_opensave_custom_filter;
8171
8172 QCheckBox* checkBoxCustomFilter[200];
8173
8174 for (std_vector<std_string>_size_type i=0; i<extensions.size(); i++) {
8175 checkBoxCustomFilter[i] = QCheckBox(extensions[i],
8176 groupBoxCustomFilter);
8177 bool checked = dialog.opensave_custom_filter.contains
8178 "*."+extensions[i],
8179 Qt_CaseInsensitive);
8180 checkBoxCustomFilter[i]_set_checked(checked);
8181 connect(checkBoxCustomFilter[i], stateChanged(int)), this,
8182 checkBoxCustomFilterStateChanged(int)));
8183 }
8184
8185 QPushButton* buttonCustomFilterSelectAll = QPushButton(translate("Select All"), groupBoxCustomFilter);
8186 connect(buttonCustomFilterSelectAll, clicked(), buttonCustomFilterSelectAllClicked()));
8187 for (std_vector<std_string>_size_type i=0; i<extensions.size(); i++) {
8188 connect(buttonCustomFilterSelectAll(bool)), checkBoxCustomFilter[i], setChecked(bool)));
8189 }
8190
8191 QPushButton* buttonCustomFilterClearAll = QPushButton("Clear All", groupBoxCustomFilter);
8192 connect(buttonCustomFilterClearAll, clicked(), buttonCustomFilterClearAllClicked()));
8193 for (std_vector<std_string>_size_type i=0; i<extensions.size(); i++) {
8194 connect(buttonCustomFilterClearAll(bool)), checkBoxCustomFilter[i], setChecked(bool)));
8195 }
8196
8197 QGridLayout* gridLayoutCustomFilter = QGridLayout(groupBoxCustomFilter);
8198 for (int i=0; i<10; i++)
8199 for (int j=0; j<10; j++) {
8200 if (10*i+j >= extensions.size()) {
8201 break;
8202 }
8203 gridLayoutCustomFilter->add_widget(checkBoxCustomFilter[10*i+j], j, i, EMB_ALIGN_LEFT);
8204 }
8205 gridLayoutCustomFilter->add_widget(buttonCustomFilterSelectAll, 0, 6, EMB_ALIGN_LEFT);
8206 gridLayoutCustomFilter->add_widget(buttonCustomFilterClearAll, 1, 6, EMB_ALIGN_LEFT);
8207 gridLayoutCustomFilter->setColumnStretch(6,1);

10299
10320static void
10321actuator(char command_line[200])
10322{
10323 char argv[11][200];
10324 int argc = 0;
10325 c_split(command_line, &argc, argv);
10326 const char *cmd = argv[0];
10327
10328 if (n_views > 0) {
10329 add_to_undo_history(&(active_view->undo_history), command_line);
10330 }
10331
10332 /* Command/argument seperation is done in order to reduce the number of
10333 * checks on every click before an action can run.
10334 *
10335 * File actions can be grouped under starts_with "file" etc.
10336 */
10337 log_debug(command_line);
10338
10339 /* Try to keep these if conditions alphabetical within each
10340 * indentation level.
10341 *
10342 * For actions with less than 5 lines of code, don't call a seperate
10343 * "*_action" function.
10344 */
10345 if (streq(cmd, "about")) {
10346 settings.show_about_dialog = true;
10347 return;
10348 }
10349 if (streq(cmd, "alert")) {
10350 /* settings.show_alert = true; */
10351 return;
10352 }
10353 if (streq(cmd, "arc")) {
10354 arc_action();
10355 return;
10356 }
10357 if (streq(cmd, "circle")) {
10358 circle_action();
10359 return;
10360 }
10361 if (streq(cmd, "changelog")) {
10362 /* settings.show_changelog = true; */
10363 return;
10364 }
10365 if (streq(cmd, "close")) {
10366 close_action();
10367 return;
10368 }
10369 if (streq(cmd, "copy")) {
10370 copy_action();
10371 return;
10372 }
10373 if (streq(cmd, "cut")) {
10374 cut_action();
10375 return;
10376 }
10377 if (streq(cmd, "day")) {
10378 /*
10379 if (active_view != NULL) {
10380 active_view->setBackgroundColor(qRgb(255,255,255));
10381 active_view->setCrossHairColor(qRgb(0,0,0));
10382 active_view->setGridColor(qRgb(0,0,0));
10383 }
10384 */
10385 return;
10386 }
10387 if (streq(cmd, "debug")) {
10388 if (strlen(cmd) > 6) {
10389 log_debug(command_line + 6);
10390 }
10391 return;
10392 }
10393 if (streq(cmd, "designdetails")) {
10394 settings.show_details_dialog = true;
10395 return;
10396 }
10397 if (streq(cmd, "donothing")) {
10398 log_debug("This action intentionally does nothing.");
10399 return;
10400 }
10401 if (streq(cmd, "editor")) {
10402 settings.show_editor = true;
10403 return;
10404 }
10405 if (streq(cmd, "exit") || streq(cmd, "quit")) {
10406 exit_action();
10407 return;
10408 }
10409 if (streq(cmd, "check-for-updates")) {
10410 printf("Visit https://libembroidery.org for information about new releases.\n");
10411 printf("Your version is: %s.\n", settings.version);
10412 return;
10413 }
10414 if (streq(cmd, "save")) {
10415 if (active_view != NULL) {
10416 embPattern_writeAuto(active_view->pattern, active_view->filename);
10417 }
10418 return;
10419 }
10420 if (streq(cmd, "platform")) {
10421 char s[200];
10422 platform_string(s);
10423 printf("%s\n", s);
10424 return;
10425 }
10426 if (streq(cmd, "settingsdialog")) {
10427 settings.show_settings_editor = true;
10428 return;
10429 }
10430 if (streq(cmd, "simulate")) {
10431 if (active_view != NULL) {
10432 active_view->simulate = true;
10433 active_view->simulation_start = clock();
10434 }
10435 return;
10436 }
10437
10438 if (streq(cmd, "ellipse")) {
10439 ellipse_action();
10440 return;
10441 }
10442 if (streq(cmd, "error")) {
10443 error_action(argv[1]);
10444 return;
10445 }
10446 if (streq(cmd, "help")) {
10447 error_action(argv[1]);
10448 return;
10449 }
10450 if (streq(cmd, "icon")) {
10451 icon_action(atoi(argv[1]));
10452 return;
10453 }
10454 if (streq(cmd, "new")) {
10455 new_file_action();
10456 return;
10457 }
10458 if (streq(cmd, "night")) {
10462 /*
10463 if (active_view) {
10464 active_view->setBackgroundColor(qRgb(0,0,0));
10465 active_view->setCrossHairColor(qRgb(255,255,255));
10466 active_view->setGridColor(qRgb(255,255,255));
10467 }
10468 */
10469 return;
10470 }
10471 if (streq(cmd, "open")) {
10472 open_file_action(argc-1, argv+1);
10473 return;
10474 }
10475 if (streq(cmd, "pan")) {
10476 pan_action(argv[1]);
10477 return;
10478 }
10479 if (streq(cmd, "paste")) {
10480 paste_action();
10481 return;
10482 }
10483 if (streq(cmd, "print")) {
10484 print_action();
10485 return;
10486 }
10487 if (streq(cmd, "rectangle")) {
10488 rectangle_action();
10489 return;
10490 }
10491 if (streq(cmd, "redo")) {
10492 redo_action();
10493 return;
10494 }
10495 if (streq(cmd, "undo")) {
10496 undo_action();
10497 return;
10498 }
10499 if (streq(cmd, "vulcanize")) {
10500 vulcanize_action();
10501 return;
10502 }
10503 if (streq(cmd, "window")) {
10504 if (argc < 2) {
10505 /* \todo missing argument error */
10506 }
10507 else {
10508 window_action(argv[1]);
10509 }
10510 return;
10511 }
10512 if (streq(cmd, "zoom")) {
10513 if (argc < 2) {
10514 /* \todo missing argument error */
10515 }
10516 else {
10517 zoom_action(argv[1]);
10518 }
10519 return;

11482static void
11483open_file_action(int argc, char argv[10][200])
11484{
11485 if (argc == 0) {
11486 settings.show_open_file_dialog = true;
11487 }
11488 else {
11489 for (int i=1; i<argc; i++) {
11490 if (n_views < 50) {
11491 views[n_views] = init_view();
11492 strcpy(views[n_views].filename, argv[i]);
11493 embPattern_readAuto(views[n_views].pattern, views[n_views].filename);
11494 settings.pattern_index = n_views;
11495 active_view = &(views[n_views]);
11496 n_views++;
11497 }
11498 else {
11499 }
11500 }
11501 }
11502 /*
11503 log_debug("openFile()");
11504
11505 char *List files;
11506 bool preview = settings_opensave_open_thumbnail;
11507 openFilesPath = settings_opensave_recent_directory;
11508
11509 // Check to see if this from the recent files list
11510 if (recent) {
11511 files.append(recentFile);
11512 openFilesSelected(files);
11513 }
11514 else {
11515 if (!preview) {
11516 \todo set getOpenFileNames' selectedFilter parameter from settings_opensave_open_format");
11517 files = QFileDialog_getOpenFileNames(translate("Open"), openFilesPath, formatFilterOpen);
11518 openFilesSelected(files);
11519 }
11520 else {
11521 PreviewDialog* openDialog = PreviewDialog(translate("Open w/Preview"), openFilesPath, formatFilterOpen);
11522 \todo set openDialog->selectNameFilter(const char * filter) from settings_opensave_open_format");
11523 connect(openDialog, filesSelected(const char *List&), openFilesSelected(const char *List&)));
11524 openDialog->exec();
11525 }
11526 }
11527
11528 openFileSelected
11529
11530 bool doOnce = true;
11531
11532 if (filesToOpen.count()) {
11533 for (int i = 0; i < filesToOpen.count(); i++) {
11534 if (!validFileFormat(filesToOpen[i])) {
11535 continue;
11536 }
11537
11538 SubView* existing = findView(filesToOpen[i]);
11539 if (existing) {
11540 active_view->setActiveSubWindow(existing);
11541 continue;
11542 }
11543
11544 //The docIndex doesn't need increased as it is only used for unnamed files
11545 numOfDocs++;
11546 View* mdiWin = View(docIndex, mainWin, mdiArea, SubWindow);
11547 connect(mdiWin, sendCloseMdiWin(View*), onCloseMdiWin(View*)));
11548 connect(mdiArea, subWindowActivated(SubView*), onWindowActivated(SubView*)));
11549
11550 //Make sure the toolbars/etc... are shown before doing their zoomExtents
11551 if (doOnce) { updateMenuToolbarStatusbar(); doOnce = false; }
11552
11553 if (mdiWin->loadFile(filesToOpen.at(i))) {
11554 statusbar_showMessage(translate("File(s) loaded"), 2000);
11555 mdiWin->show();
11556 mdiWin->showMaximized();
11557 //Prevent duplicate entries in the recent files list
11558 if (!settings_opensave_recent_list_of_files.contains(filesToOpen.at(i), CaseInsensitive))
11559 {
11560 settings_opensave_recent_list_of_files.prepend(filesToOpen.at(i));
11561 }
11562 //Move the recent file to the top of the list
11563 else
11564 {
11565 settings_opensave_recent_list_of_files.removeAll(filesToOpen.at(i));
11566 settings_opensave_recent_list_of_files.prepend(filesToOpen.at(i));
11567 }
11568 settings_opensave_recent_directory = QFileInfo(filesToOpen.at(i)).absolutePath();
11569
11570 if (active_view) {
11571 active_view->recalculateLimits();
11572 actuator("zoom extents");
11573 }
11574 }
11575 else {
11576 mdiWin->close();
11577 }
11578 }
11579 }
11580
11581 windowMenuAboutToShow();
11582
11583 log_debug("View loadFile()");
11584
11585 unsigned int tmpColor = getCurrentColor();
11586
11587 QFile file(fileName);
11588 if (!file.open(QFile_ReadOnly | QFile_Text)) {
11589 warning_messagebox(translate("Error reading file"),
11590 translate("Cannot read file %1:\n%2.")
11591 .arg(fileName)
11592 .arg(file.errorString()));
11593 return false;
11594 }
11595
11596 char * ext = fileExtension(fileName);
11597 log_debug("ext: %s", ext));
11598
11599 //Read
11600 EmbPattern* p = embPattern_create();
11601 if (!p) {
11602 printf("Could not allocate memory for embroidery pattern\n");
11603 exit(1);
11604 }
11605 int readSuccessful = 0;
11606 char * readError;
11607 int reader = emb_identify_format(fileName));
11608 if (reader < 0) {
11609 readSuccessful = 0;
11610 readError = "Unsupported read file type: " + fileName;
11611 log_debug("Unsupported read file type: " + fileName.toStdString());
11612 }
11613 else {
11614 readSuccessful = embPattern_read(p, fileName), reader);
11615 if (!readSuccessful) {
11616 readError = "Reading file was unsuccessful: " + fileName;
11617 log_debug("Reading file was unsuccessful: " + fileName.toStdString());
11618 }
11619 }
11620 if (!readSuccessful) {
11621 messagebox(MSG_WARNING, translate("Error reading pattern"), translate(readError)));
11622 messagebox(MSG_WARNING, translate("Error reading pattern"), translate("Cannot read pattern"));
11623 }
11624 else {
11625 \todo test embPattern_moveStitchListToPolylines more.
11626 embPattern_moveStitchListToPolylines(p);
11627 int stitchCount = p->stitchList->count;
11628 EmbPath path;
11629
11630
11631 setCurrentFile(fileName);
11632 statusbar_showMessage("File loaded.");
11633 char * stitches;
11634 stitches.setNum(stitchCount);
11635
11636 if (settings_grid_load_from_file) {
11637 \todo Josh, provide me a hoop size and/or grid spacing from the pattern.
11638 }
11639 }
11640 embPattern_free(p);
11641
11642 //Clear the undo stack so it is not possible to undo past this point.
11643 gview->undo_stack->clear();
11644
11645 setCurrentColor(tmpColor);
11646
11647 fileWasLoaded = true;
11648 setUndoCleanIcon(fileWasLoaded);
11649 return fileWasLoaded;
11650 */
11651}

11681static void
11682pan_action(const char *mode)
11683{
11684 if (streq(mode, "realtime")) {
11685 /* active_view->panningRealTimeActive = true; */
11686 return;
11687 }
11688 if (streq(mode, "point")) {
11689 /* active_view->panningPointActive = true; */
11690 return;
11691 }
11692 if (streq(mode, "left")) {
11693 active_view->origin.x += active_view->scale;
11694 /*
11695 horizontalscrollbar()->setValue(horizontalscrollbar()->value() + panDistance);
11696 updateMouseCoords(viewMousePoint);
11697 */
11698 return;
11699 }
11700 if (streq(mode, "right")) {
11701 active_view->origin.x -= active_view->scale;
11702 /*
11703 horizontalscrollbar()->setValue(horizontalscrollbar()->value() - panDistance);
11704 updateMouseCoords(viewMousePoint);
11705 */
11706 return;
11707 }
11708 if (streq(mode, "up")) {
11709 active_view->origin.y += active_view->scale;
11710 /*
11711 verticalscrollbar()->setValue(verticalscrollbar()->value() + panDistance);
11712 updateMouseCoords(viewMousePoint);
11713 */
11714 return;
11715 }
11716 if (streq(mode, "down")) {
11717 active_view->origin.y -= active_view->scale;
11718 /*
11719 verticalscrollbar()->setValue(verticalscrollbar()->value() - panDistance);
11720 updateMouseCoords(viewMousePoint);
11721 */
11722 return;
11723 }
11724}

12858static void
12859calculate_distance_action(void)
12860{
12861 /*
12862 EmbLine line;
12863 line.start.x = results[0];
12864 line.start.y = results[1];
12865 line.end.x = results[2];
12866 line.end.y = results[3];
12867
12868 return embVector_length(embLine_vector(line));
12869 */
12870}
12871
12879EmbReal
12880embVector_perpendicularDistance(EmbVector p, EmbLine line)
12881{
12882 EmbVector direction = embVector_subtract(line.end, line.start);
12883 EmbReal length = embVector_length(direction);
12884 EmbVector p_start = embVector_subtract(line.start, p);
12885 EmbReal v = embVector_cross(direction, p_start);
12886 return v / length;
12887}

13992EmbReal
13993perpendicular_distance(EmbVector p, EmbLine line)
13994{
13995 EmbVector iPoint;
13996 EmbVector norm;
13997 EmbVector delta = embVector_subtract(p, line.start);
13998 /*
13999 norm = embLine_normal(line);
14000 norm = embVector_add(norm, delta);
14001 norm.intersects(line, &iPoint);
14002 return embVector_distance(p, iPoint);
14003 */
14004 return 0.0;
14005}

14691static void
14692load_formats(void)
14693{
14694 /*
14695 char stable, unstable;
14696 char * supportedReaders = "All Supported Files (";
14697 char * individualReaders = "All Files (*);;";
14698 char * supportedWriters = "All Supported Files (";

14700 char * supportedStr;
14701 char * individualStr;
14702
14703 //\todo Stable Only (Settings Option)
14704 //stable = 'S'; unstable = 'S';
14705
14706 //Stable + Unstable
14707 stable = 'S'; unstable = 'U';
14708
14709 const char* extension = 0;
14710 const char* description = 0;
14711 char readerState;
14712 char writerState;
14713
14714 EmbFormatList* curFormat = 0;
14715 for (int i=0; i < numberOfFormats; i++) {
14716 extension = formatTable[i].extension;
14717 description = formatTable[i].description;
14718 readerState = formatTable[i].reader_state;
14719 writerState = formatTable[i].writer_state;
14720
14721 char * upperExt = char *(extension).toUpper();
14722 supportedStr = "*" + upperExt + " ";
14723 individualStr = upperExt.replace(".", "") + " - " + description + " (*" + extension + ");;";
14724 if (readerState == stable || readerState == unstable) {
14725 //Exclude color file formats from open dialogs
14726 if (upperExt != "COL" && upperExt != "EDR" && upperExt != "INF" && upperExt != "RGB") {
14727 supportedReaders.append(supportedStr);
14728 individualReaders.append(individualStr);
14729 }
14730 }
14731 if (writerState == stable || writerState == unstable) {
14732 supportedWriters.append(supportedStr);
14733 individualWriters.append(individualStr);
14734 }
14735 }
14736
14737 supportedReaders.append(");;");
14738 supportedWriters.append(");;");
14739
14740 formatFilterOpen = supportedReaders + individualReaders;
14741 formatFilterSave = supportedWriters + individualWriters;
14742
14743 //\todo Fixup custom filter
14744 char * custom = getSettingsCustomFilter();
14745 if (custom.contains("supported", CaseInsensitive))
14746 custom = ""; //This will hide it
14747 else if (!custom.contains("*", CaseInsensitive))
14748 custom = ""; //This will hide it
14749 else
14750 custom = "Custom Filter(" + custom + ");;";
14751
14752 return translate(custom + supported + all));
14753 */

15205static void
15206embCircle_prompt(UiObject *global, const char *str)
15207{
15208 if (n_views == 0) {
15209 return;
15210 }
15211
15212 printf("%s", str);
15213
15214 if (global->mode == CIRCLE_MODE_1P_RAD) {
15215 /*
15216 if (isnan(global.x1)) {
15217 if (streq(str, "2P") {
15218 //\todo Probably should add additional translate calls here.
15219 global->mode = "CIRCLE_MODE_2P";
15220 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify first end point of circle's diameter: "));
15221 }
15222 else if (streq(str, "3P") {
15223 global->mode = "CIRCLE_MODE_3P";
15224 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify first point of circle: "));
15225 }
15226 else if (streq(str, "T" || streq(str, "TTR") {
15227 global->mode = "CIRCLE_MODE_TTR";
15228 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify point on object for first tangent of circle: "));
15229 }
15230 else {
15231 std_vector<char *> strList = str.split(",");
15232 if (isnan(strList[0]) || isnan(strList[1])) {
15233 alert(translate("Point or option keyword required."));
15234 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify center point for circle or [3P/2P/Ttr (tan tan radius)]: "));
15235 }
15236 else {
15237 global.x1 = Number(strList[0]);
15238 global.y1 = Number(strList[1]);
15239 global.cx = global.x1;
15240 global.cy = global.y1;
15241 add_rubber("CIRCLE");
15242 setRubberMode("CIRCLE_1P_RAD");
15243 setRubberPoint("CIRCLE_CENTER", global.cx, global.cy);
15244 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify radius of circle or [Diameter]: "));
15245 }
15246 }
15247 }
15248 else {
15249 if (streq(str, "D" || streq(str, "DIAMETER") {
15250 //\todo Probably should add additional translate calls here.
15251 global->mode = "CIRCLE_MODE_1P_DIA";
15252 setRubberMode("CIRCLE_1P_DIA");
15253 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify diameter of circle: "));
15254 }
15255 else {
15256 float num = Number(str);
15257 if (isnan(num)) {
15258 alert(translate("Requires numeric radius, point on circumference, or \"D\"."));
15259 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify radius of circle or [Diameter]: "));
15260 }
15261 else {
15262 global.rad = num;
15263 global.x2 = global.x1 + global.rad;
15264 global.y2 = global.y1;
15265 setRubberPoint("CIRCLE_RADIUS", global.x2, global.y2);
15266 vulcanize();
15267 end_command();
15268 }
15269 }
15270 }
15271 }
15272 case MODE_1P_DIA) {
15273 if (isnan(global.x1)) {
15274 error("CIRCLE", translate("This should never happen."));
15275 }
15276 if (isnan(global.x2)) {
15277 float num = Number(str);
15278 if (isnan(num)) {
15279 alert(translate("Requires numeric distance or second point."));
15280 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify diameter of circle: "));
15281 }
15282 else {
15283 global.dia = num;
15284 global.x2 = global.x1 + global.dia;
15285 global.y2 = global.y1;
15286 setRubberPoint("CIRCLE_DIAMETER", global.x2, global.y2);
15287 vulcanize();
15288 end_command();
15289 }
15290 }
15291 else {
15292 error("CIRCLE", translate("This should never happen."));
15293 }
15294 }
15295 case MODE_2P) {
15296 if (isnan(global.x1)) {
15297 std_vector<char *> strList = str.split(",");
15298 if (isnan(strList[0]) || isnan(strList[1])) {
15299 alert(translate("Invalid point."));
15300 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify first end point of circle's diameter: "));
15301 }
15302 else {
15303 global.x1 = Number(strList[0]);
15304 global.y1 = Number(strList[1]);
15305 add_rubber("CIRCLE");
15306 setRubberMode("CIRCLE_2P");
15307 setRubberPoint("CIRCLE_TAN1", global.x1, global.y1);
15308 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify second end point of circle's diameter: "));
15309 }
15310 }
15311 else if (isnan(global.x2)) {
15312 std_vector<char *> strList = str.split(",");
15313 if (isnan(strList[0]) || isnan(strList[1])) {
15314 alert(translate("Invalid point."));
15315 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify second end point of circle's diameter: "));
15316 }
15317 else {
15318 global.x2 = Number(strList[0]);
15319 global.y2 = Number(strList[1]);
15320 setRubberPoint("CIRCLE_TAN2", global.x2, global.y2);
15321 vulcanize();
15322 end_command();
15323 }
15324 }
15325 else {
15326 error("CIRCLE", translate("This should never happen."));
15327 }
15328 }
15329 case MODE_3P) {
15330 if (isnan(global.x1)) {
15331 std_vector<char *> strList = str.split(",");
15332 if (isnan(strList[0]) || isnan(strList[1])) {
15333 alert(translate("Invalid point."));
15334 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify first point of circle: "));
15335 }
15336 else {
15337 global.x1 = Number(strList[0]);
15338 global.y1 = Number(strList[1]);
15339 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify second point of circle: "));
15340 }
15341 }
15342 else if (isnan(global.x2)) {
15343 std_vector<char *> strList = str.split(",");
15344 if (isnan(strList[0]) || isnan(strList[1])) {
15345 alert(translate("Invalid point."));
15346 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify second point of circle: "));
15347 }
15348 else {
15349 global.x2 = Number(strList[0]);
15350 global.y2 = Number(strList[1]);
15351 add_rubber("CIRCLE");
15352 setRubberMode("CIRCLE_3P");
15353 setRubberPoint("CIRCLE_TAN1", global.x1, global.y1);
15354 setRubberPoint("CIRCLE_TAN2", global.x2, global.y2);
15355 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify third point of circle: "));
15356 }
15357 }
15358 else if (isnan(global.x3)) {
15359 std_vector<char *> strList = str.split(",");
15360 if (isnan(strList[0]) || isnan(strList[1])) {
15361 alert(translate("Invalid point."));
15362 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify third point of circle: "));
15363 }
15364 else {
15365 global.x3 = Number(strList[0]);
15366 global.y3 = Number(strList[1]);
15367 setRubberPoint("CIRCLE_TAN3", global.x3, global.y3);
15368 vulcanize();
15369 end_command();
15370 }
15371 }
15372 else {
15373 error("CIRCLE", translate("This should never happen."));
15374 }
15375
15376 }
15377 case MODE_TTR) {
15378 todo("CIRCLE", "prompt() for TTR");
15379 */
15380 }
15381}

15398bool
15399save_save(const char *fileName)
15400{
15401 char debug_msg[200];
15402 sprintf(debug_msg, "save %s", fileName);
15403 log_debug(debug_msg);
15404 printf("%s", fileName);
15405 bool writeSuccessful = false;
15406 int i;
15407
15408 int formatType = emb_identify_format(fileName);
15409 if (formatTable[formatType].type == EMBFORMAT_UNSUPPORTED) {
15410 sprintf(debug_msg, "Unsupported write file type: %s", fileName);
15411 log_debug(debug_msg);
15412 return false;
15413 }
15414
15415 EmbPattern* pattern = embPattern_create();
15416 if (!pattern) {
15417 log_debug("Could not allocate memory for embroidery pattern");
15418 return false;
15419 }
15420
15424 /*
15425 if (formatTable[formatType].type == EMBFORMAT_STITCHONLY) {
15426 embPattern_movePolylinesToStitchList(pattern);
15427 */
15431 /*
15432 }
15433
15434 const char *s = "output";
15435 s += formatTable[formatType].extension;
15436
15437 writeSuccessful = embPattern_write(pattern, s), formatType);
15438 if (!writeSuccessful) {
15439 debug_message("Writing file %s was unsuccessful", fileName));
15440 }
15441 */
15442
15446 embPattern_free(pattern);
15447 return writeSuccessful;
15448}

15706static void
15707update_heart(EmbPath *path, UiObject global)
15708{
15709 /*
15710 EmbVector v;
15711 float two_pi = 2*Math.PI;
15712
15713 for (int i = 0; i <= numPts; i++) {
15714 float t = two_pi/numPts*i;
15715
15716 if (style == "HEART4") {
15717 v.x = cos(t)*((sin(t)*sqrt(fabs(cos(t))))/(sin(t)+7/5) - 2*sin(t) + 2);
15718 v.y = sin(t)*((sin(t)*sqrt(fabs(cos(t))))/(sin(t)+7/5) - 2*sin(t) + 2);
15719 }
15720 else if (style == "HEART5") {
15721 v.x = 16*Math.pow(sin(t), 3);
15722 v.y = 13*cos(t) - 5*cos(2*t) - 2*cos(3*t) - cos(4*t);
15723 }
15724
15725 setRubberPoint("POLYGON_POINT_" + i.toString(), v.x*xScale, v.y*yScale);
15726 }
15727

16022 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify center point or [Sidelength]: "));
16023 global->mode = MODE_CENTER_PT;
16024 }
16025 }
16026 }
16027 case MODE_CENTER_PT) {
16028 if (streq(str, "S" || streq(str, "SIDELENGTH") {
16029 global->mode = MODE_SIDE_LEN;
16030 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify start point: "));
16031 }
16032 else {
16033 std_vector<char *> strList = str.split(",");
16034 if (isnan(strList[0]) || isnan(strList[1])) {
16035 alert(translate("Point or option keyword required."));
16036 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify center point or [Sidelength]: "));
16037 }
16038 else {
16039 global.centerX = Number(strList[0]);
16040 global.centerY = Number(strList[1]);
16041 global->mode = MODE_POLYTYPE;
16042 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify polygon type [Inscribed in circle/Circumscribed around circle]") + " {" + global.polyType + "}: ");
16043 }
16044 }
16045 }
16046 case MODE_POLYTYPE) {
16047 if (streq(str, "INSCRIBED") {
16048 global->mode = MODE_INSCRIBE;
16049 global.polyType = "Inscribed";
16050 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify polygon corner point or [Distance]: "));
16051 add_rubber("POLYGON");
16052 setRubberMode("POLYGON_INSCRIBE");
16053 setRubberPoint("POLYGON_CENTER", global.centerX, global.centerY);
16054 setRubberPoint("POLYGON_NUM_SIDES", global.numSides, 0);
16055 }
16056 else if (streq(str, "CIRCUMSCRIBED") {
16057 global->mode = MODE_CIRCUMSCRIBE;
16058 global.polyType = "Circumscribed";
16059 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify polygon side point or [Distance]: "));
16060 add_rubber("POLYGON");
16061 setRubberMode("POLYGON_CIRCUMSCRIBE");
16062 setRubberPoint("POLYGON_CENTER", global.centerX, global.centerY);
16063 setRubberPoint("POLYGON_NUM_SIDES", global.numSides, 0);
16064 }
16065 else if (streq(str, "") {
16066 if (global.polyType == "Inscribed") {
16067 global->mode = MODE_INSCRIBE;
16068 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify polygon corner point or [Distance]: "));
16069 add_rubber("POLYGON");
16070 setRubberMode("POLYGON_INSCRIBE");
16071 setRubberPoint("POLYGON_CENTER", global.centerX, global.centerY);
16072 setRubberPoint("POLYGON_NUM_SIDES", global.numSides, 0);
16073 }
16074 else if (global.polyType == "Circumscribed") {
16075 global->mode = MODE_CIRCUMSCRIBE;
16076 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify polygon side point or [Distance]: "));
16077 add_rubber("POLYGON");
16078 setRubberMode("POLYGON_CIRCUMSCRIBE");
16079 setRubberPoint("POLYGON_CENTER", global.centerX, global.centerY);
16080 setRubberPoint("POLYGON_NUM_SIDES", global.numSides, 0);
16081 }
16082 else {
16083 error("POLYGON", translate("Polygon type is not Inscribed or Circumscribed."));
16084 }
16085 }
16086 else {
16087 alert(translate("Invalid option keyword."));
16088 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify polygon type [Inscribed in circle/Circumscribed around circle]") + " {" + global.polyType + "}: ");
16089 }
16090 }
16091 case MODE_INSCRIBE) {
16092 if (streq(str, "D" || streq(str, "DISTANCE") {
16093 global->mode = MODE_DISTANCE;
16094 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify distance: "));
16095 }
16096 else {
16097 std_vector<char *> strList = str.split(",");
16098 if (isnan(strList[0]) || isnan(strList[1])) {
16099 alert(translate("Point or option keyword required."));
16100 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify polygon corner point or [Distance]: "));
16101 }
16102 else {
16103 global.pointIX = Number(strList[0]);
16104 global.pointIY = Number(strList[1]);
16105 setRubberPoint("POLYGON_INSCRIBE_POINT", global.pointIX, global.pointIY);
16106 vulcanize();
16107 end_command();
16108 }
16109 }
16110 }
16111 case MODE_CIRCUMSCRIBE) {
16112 if (streq(str, "D" || streq(str, "DISTANCE") {
16113 global->mode = MODE_DISTANCE;
16114 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify distance: "));
16115 }
16116 else {
16117 std_vector<char *> strList = str.split(",");
16118 if (isnan(strList[0]) || isnan(strList[1])) {
16119 alert(translate("Point or option keyword required."));
16120 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify polygon side point or [Distance]: "));
16121 }
16122 else {
16123 global.pointCX = Number(strList[0]);
16124 global.pointCY = Number(strList[1]);
16125 setRubberPoint("POLYGON_CIRCUMSCRIBE_POINT", global.pointCX, global.pointCY);
16126 vulcanize();
16127 end_command();
16128 }
16129 }
16130 }
16131 case MODE_DISTANCE) {
16132 if (isnan(str)) {
16133 alert(translate("Requires valid numeric distance."));
16134 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify distance: "));
16135 }
16136 else {
16137 if (global.polyType == "Inscribed") {
16138 global.pointIX = global.centerX;
16139 global.pointIY = global.centerY + Number(str);
16140 setRubberPoint("POLYGON_INSCRIBE_POINT", global.pointIX, global.pointIY);
16141 vulcanize();
16142 end_command();
16143 }
16144 else if (global.polyType == "Circumscribed") {
16145 global.pointCX = global.centerX;
16146 global.pointCY = global.centerY + Number(str);
16147 setRubberPoint("POLYGON_CIRCUMSCRIBE_POINT", global.pointCX, global.pointCY);
16148 vulcanize();
16149 end_command();
16150 }
16151 else {
16152 error("POLYGON", translate("Polygon type is not Inscribed or Circumscribed."));
16153 }
16154 }
16155 }
16156 case MODE_SIDE_LEN) {
16157 todo("POLYGON", "Sidelength mode");
16158 }
16159 */
16160}

16750static void
16751rotate_click(UiObject *global, EmbVector pos)
16752{
16753 switch (global->mode) {
16754 case ROTATE_MODE_NORMAL: {
16755 /*
16756 if (global.firstRun) {
16757 global.firstRun = false;
16758 global.baseX = x;
16759 global.baseY = y;
16760 add_rubber("LINE");
16761 setRubberMode("LINE");
16762 setRubberPoint("LINE_START", global.baseX, global.baseY);
16763 previewOn("SELECTED", "ROTATE", global.baseX, global.baseY, 0);
16764 append_prompt_history();
16765 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify rotation angle or [Reference]: "));
16766 }
16767 else {
16768 global.destX = x;
16769 global.destY = y;
16770 global.angle = calculateAngle(global.baseX, global.baseY, global.destX, global.destY);
16771 append_prompt_history();
16772 rotateSelected(global.baseX, global.baseY, global.angle);
16773 previewOff();

17635
17639UiObject
17640snowflake_main(void)
17641{
17642 UiObject global = generic_design_init();
17643 global.numPoints = 2048;
17644 global.minPoints = 64;
17645 global.maxPoints = 8192;
17646 global.scale.x = 0.04f;
17647 global.scale.y = 0.04f;
17648 global.mode = SNOWFLAKE_MODE_NUM_POINTS;
17649
17650 /*
17651 add_rubber("POLYGON");
17652 setRubberMode("POLYGON");
17653 updateSnowflake(path, global);
17654 spareRubber("POLYGON");
17655 */
17656 end_command();
17657 return global;
17658}
17659
17663UiObject
17664snowflake_click(UiObject global, EmbVector position)
17665{
17666
17667 return global;
17668}
17669
17676UiObject
17677snowflake_move(UiObject global, EmbVector delta)
17678{
17679 global.center = embVector_add(global.center, delta);
17680 return global;
17681}

18348
18352UiObject
18353generic_design_init(void)
18354{
18355 UiObject design;
18356 init_command();
18357 clear_selection();
18358 design.center.x = 0.0f;
18359 design.center.y = 0.0f;
18360 for (int i=0; i<10; i++) {
18361 design.controlPoints[i].x = 0.0f;
18362 design.controlPoints[i].y = 0.0f;
18363 }
18364 return design;
18365}
18366
18372UiObject
18373star_main(void)
18374{
18375 char msg[200];
18376 UiObject global = generic_design_init();
18377 global.numPoints = 5;
18378 global.mode = STAR_MODE_NUM_POINTS;
18379 sprintf(msg, "%s {%d}: ", translate("Enter number of star points"), global.numPoints);
18380 set_prompt_prefix(msg);
18381 return global;
18382}
18383
18387UiObject
18388star_click(UiObject global, EmbVector pos)
18389{
18390 switch (global.mode) {
18391 case STAR_MODE_NUM_POINTS:
18392 /* Do nothing, the prompt controls this. */
18393 break;
18394 case STAR_MODE_CENTER_PT: {
18395 /*
18396 global.cx = x;
18397 global.cy = y;
18398 global->mode = MODE_RAD_OUTER;
18399 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify outer radius of star: "));
18400 add_rubber("POLYGON");
18401 setRubberMode("POLYGON");
18402 updateStar(global.cx, global.cy);
18403 enableMoveRapidFire();
18404 */
18405 break;
18406 }
18407 case STAR_MODE_RAD_OUTER: {
18408 /*
18409 global.x1 = x;
18410 global.y1 = y;
18411 global->mode = MODE_RAD_INNER;
18412 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify inner radius of star: "));
18413 updateStar(global.x1, global.y1);
18414 */
18415 break;
18416 }
18417 case STAR_MODE_RAD_INNER: {
18418 /*
18419 global.x2 = x;
18420 global.y2 = y;
18421 disableMoveRapidFire();
18422 updateStar(global.x2, global.y2);
18423 spareRubber("POLYGON");
18424 end_command();
18425 */
18426 break;
18427 }
18428 default:
18429 break;
18430 }
18431}

18528 else {
18529 global.point1.x = Number(strList[0]);
18530 global.point1.y = Number(strList[1]);
18531 global->mode = MODE_RAD_INNER;
18532 set_prompt_prefix(translate("Specify inner radius of star: "));
18533 updateStar(qsnapX(), qsnapY());
18534 }
18535 */
18536 break;
18537 default:
18538 break;
18539 }
18540}
18541
18545static void
18546updateStar(EmbPath *path, UiObject global)
18547{
18548 float distOuter = 0.0;
18549 float distInner = 0.0;
18550 float angOuter = 0.0;
18551
18552 if (n_views == 0) {
18553 return;
18554 }
18555
18556 switch (global.mode) {
18557 case STAR_MODE_RAD_OUTER: {
18558 EmbVector delta;
18559 delta = embVector_subtract(global.center, global.controlPoints[1]);
18560 angOuter = embVector_angle(delta);
18561 distOuter = embVector_distance(global.center, global.controlPoints[1]);
18562 distInner = distOuter/2.0;
18563 break;
18564 }
18565 case STAR_MODE_RAD_INNER: {
18566 EmbVector delta;
18567 delta = embVector_subtract(global.center, global.controlPoints[0]);
18568 angOuter = embVector_angle(delta);
18569 distOuter = embVector_distance(global.center, global.controlPoints[0]);
18570 distInner = embVector_distance(global.center, global.controlPoints[1]);
18571 break;
18572 }
18573 default:
18574 break;
18575 }
18576
18577 //Calculate the Star Points
18578 float angInc = 360.0/(global.numPoints*2);
18579
18580 for (int i = 0; i < (int)global.numPoints*2; i++) {
18581 EmbVector point;
18582 EmbReal angle = (angOuter+(angInc*i)) * embConstantPi / 180.0;
18583 if (i%2 == 1) {
18584 point.x = distOuter*cos(angle);
18585 point.y = distOuter*sin(angle);
18586 }
18587 else {
18588 point.x = distInner*cos(angle);
18589 point.y = distInner*sin(angle);
18590 }
18591 printf("%f %f", point.x, point.y);
18592 /*
18593 setRubberPoint("POLYGON_POINT_" + i.toString(), global.cx + xx, global.cy + yy);
18594 */
18595 }
18596 /*
18597 setRubberText("POLYGON_NUM_POINTS", (global.numPoints*2 - 1).toString());
18598 */
18599}
